And since wage and salary costs have risen 6.7 percent since 2022, the median labor income of full-time working undocumented immigrants today is about $46,200. Some work part-time, so we also used data on the share of men and women working part-time and the shares of male and female unauthorized immigrants to estimate that 16.6 percent of employed unauthorized immigrants work part-time (nearly 1.2 million) and 83.7 percent work full-time (almost 6 million). title: 'GOLDEN AGE': President Trump delivers inaugural address
author: @fwnm
comment:
Oh, Do Spare Us the Drama of American Affairs

One is compelled to observe, with an air of dispassionate resignation, the recent swearing-in of one Donald Trump as President of the United States. And yet, one cannot help but wonderâ€”why, precisely, should the civilised world concern itself overly with the goings-on across the Atlantic? For while the Americans may delight in their delusions of grandeur, we Europeans remain the rightful custodians of the true cradle of Western civilisation. It was upon the storied soils of Europe that democracy, philosophy, and the arts flourished long before the New World was so much as a whisper on the horizon. And yet, the United States, in its adolescent hubris, now fancies itself the torchbearer of these values even as it tramples them underfoot.

Let us be crystal clear: Europe is, and shall remain, the locus of global significance. It is here, amidst the venerable capitals of culture and intellect, that the great movements of history are forged. If the Americans are determined to chase the phantoms of isolationism and vulgar populism, then so be it. The European Union, that most enlightened of modern constructs, must now rise as a robust counterweight to the faltering republic across the sea. Militarily, economically, andâ€”dare one say itâ€”culturally, we Europeans surpass the Americans by orders of magnitude. Where they bicker, we unite; where they regress, we innovate.

And yet, one cannot help but observe with no small measure of disdain the Americans' unrelenting obsession with fossil fuels. It is as though the United States has decided to shroud itself in the soot of a bygone era, wholly indifferent to the winds of progress that now drive the world towards sustainability. The barbarous spectacle of pipelines and coal mines as symbols of national pride is, frankly, an affront to reason itself. In Europe, of course, we have long since embraced the future, leading the charge in renewable energy and environmental stewardship. Whilst they cling stubbornly to their barrels of crude like relics of a civilisation in terminal decline, we Europeans are busy crafting a cleaner, greener destiny.

As for NATO, alas, its time has passed. What purpose remains in tying the fortunes of Europe to a declining power mired in self-inflicted chaos? The European Union, in its wisdom, must assume the mantle of leadership for the Western world. An independent European defence architecture is not merely desirable but inevitable, and it is high time the anachronism of Ramstein Air Base is consigned to history. Let it be closed, and let the stars of Europe ascend in its stead.

In summation, the message is clear: God save the European Union. EU first!
